<header><div class="container"><h2>Fresh Mango Juice</h2><div>Simple recipe, nutrition facts, and tips</div></div></header>
<main class="container">
<section class="card" aria-labelledby="intro">
<h1 id="intro">Why mango juice?</h1>
<p class="lead">Mangoes are rich in vitamin C, beta-carotene, and natural sweetness ‚Äî perfect for a quick energizing drink.</p>
<div class="grid">
<div>
<h3>Ingredients</h3>
<ul>
<li>2 ripe mangoes (peeled & cubed)</li>
<li>1 cup cold water or coconut water</li>
<li>1 tbsp honey or to taste (optional)</li>
<li>Ice cubes and a squeeze of lime</li>
</ul>
<h3>Directions</h3>
<ol>
<li>Blend mango cubes and water until smooth.</li>
<li>Sweeten with honey if desired, add lime and ice, then blend briefly.</li>
<li>Strain for smoother texture or enjoy as is.</li>
</ol>
</div>
<aside class="card" style="padding:12px">
<img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1601004890684-d8cbf643f5f2?w=800&q=60" alt="Fresh mango juice">
<p style="margin:10px 0 0;font-size:.95rem">Tip: Use chilled mango and keep portions small to retain freshness.</p>
</aside>
</div>
</section>
<section class="card" style="margin-top:16px" aria-labelledby="benefits">
<h3 id="benefits">Health benefits</h3>
<p>Mango juice provides antioxidants, supports immunity, and can be a healthy alternative to sugary drinks when prepared at home.</p>
